analysis: The documents consist of executive orders that designate various international organizations as public international organizations, granting them certain privileges, exemptions, and immunities under the International Organizations Immunities Act. The orders also often state that the designation is not intended to abridge any privileges or immunities the organizations may have acquired by treaty or congressional action. Some orders also revoke previous executive orders related to similar designations or make amendments to existing orders.
title: International Organizations Granted Immunities and Privileges
